snippet: Adli Mansour, the chief justice of the Egyptian Supreme Constitutional Court who will succeed the ousted President Mohamed Morsi, has no prior presence on Egypt’s political or public scene.
abstract: Adli Mansour, chief justice of Egyptian Supreme Constitutional Court who will succeed ousted Pres Mohamed Morsi, has no prior presence on Egypt’s political or public scene, raising concern among experts who say he may serve as little more than a figurehead.
